==Scots==

===Etymology===
Vartiant of the Scots word ''[[lawlands]]'' meaning [[lowlands]] of [[Scotland]].

===Proper noun===
{{sco-proper noun}}

# A dialect of the [[Scots]] language, a Germanic language closely related to [[English]] and descended from northern dialects of [[Old English]], that uses [[Gaelic]] loan words. It is spoken in parts of [[Scotland]], in particular the south, central and [[Doric]] dialects.

